 <H1>Disk Space Management</H1> 
 <P><UL></P>

<P><LI><H2>Lowest layer of DBMS software manages space on disk.
</H2></P>

<P></UL><UL></P>

<P><LI><H2>Higher levels call upon this layer to:
</H2></P>

<P><UL></P>

<P><LI>allocate/de-allocate a page
<LI>read/write a page
</UL></UL><UL></P>

<P><LI><H2>Request for a sequence of pages must be satisfied by allocating the pages sequentially on disk!  Higher levels don’t need to know how this is done, or how free space is managed.</H2></P>

<P></UL></P>

